commit.message:
mn10300.md (call, call_value): Use "call" instead of "calls" for calls to named functions.

        * mn10300.md (call, call_value): Use "call" instead of "calls"
        for calls to named functions.

From-SVN: r14228

files.patch:
@@ -1139,7 +1139,13 @@
   [(call (mem:QI (match_operand:SI 0 "call_address_operand" "aS"))
 	 (match_operand:SI 1 "general_operand" "g"))]
   ""
-  "calls %C0"
+  "*
+{
+  if (REG_P (operands[0]))
+    return \"calls %C0\";
+  else
+    return \"call %C0,[],0\";
+}"
   [(set_attr "cc" "clobber")])
 
 ;; Call subroutine, returning value in operand 0
@@ -1165,7 +1171,13 @@
 	(call (mem:QI (match_operand:SI 1 "call_address_operand" "aS"))
 	      (match_operand:SI 2 "general_operand" "g")))]
   ""
-  "calls %C1"
+  "*
+{
+  if (REG_P (operands[1]))
+    return \"calls %C1\";
+  else
+    return \"call %C1,[],0\";
+}"
   [(set_attr "cc" "clobber")])
 
 (define_expand "untyped_call"
